{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The classic board game Puerto Rico can be time consuming to score since it has so many ways to get points. Having heard about React from Jordan Rhea (<a href=\"https://github.com/rheajt\">rheajt</a> on Github), I decided to try to make a scoring webapp.</p>\n<p>Through the use of many tutorials, I was able to understand the design principles of React, such as components and state flow, and use them to design the components and put them together. For visual design, I used Reactstrap, a package based on Bootstrap, for its easy styling and layout options.</p>\n<p>The webapp proved a success with my gaming group, and spurred me on to try other software design projects.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Update</strong>: I redesigned the entire state system for the app to use Redux, which should make it easier to add in buildings from the expansion later.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Puerto Rico Scoresheet","subtitle":"Board game scoring webapp","tags":["javascript","react","redux"],"category":"Web App","project":"https://google.com","demo":"https://google.com","date":"24 January, 2018","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='118' viewBox='0 0 400 118' version='1'%3e%3cpath d='M202 8c-2 4 1 8 4 6h5a1645 1645 0 0 0 6-2l1 1c1 2 3 3 4 0h1c1 2 5 2 5 0l1-2 1 2c0 2 0 2 1 1h1c1 2 7 1 8-2h1l1 2 1-2-2-2c-4 1-12 0-13-1s-1-1-1 2c0 1 0 2-1 1 0-2-1-2-11-2h-10c1 0 0-2-2-2h-1' fill='lightgray' fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.9841269841269842,"src":"/ryanoldford-dot-com/static/c35a42434cdb5fdb60502ff8088f9e0a/51c04/puerto-rico-scoresheet.png","srcSet":"/ryanoldford-dot-com/static/c35a42434cdb5fdb60502ff8088f9e0a/34596/puerto-rico-scoresheet.png 125w,\n/ryanoldford-dot-com/static/c35a42434cdb5fdb60502ff8088f9e0a/c0df5/puerto-rico-scoresheet.png 250w,\n/ryanoldford-dot-com/static/c35a42434cdb5fdb60502ff8088f9e0a/51